61.6	Wardenclyffe_Tower	Wardenclyffe Tower	Wardenclyffe Tower (1901â€“1917) also known as the Tesla Tower, was an early wireless telecommunications tower designed by Nikola Tesla and intended for commercial trans-Atlantic wireless telephony, broadcasting, and to demonstrate the transmission of power without interconnecting wires. The core facility was not completed due to financial problems and was never fully operational.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/ff/BrochureWardenclyffe_.PNG/333px-BrochureWardenclyffe_.PNG
